<head><title>Cafe Pacific: Nius Country Profiles: Tonga</title></head>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FF6EC7">
<A HREF="../david_prof.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/tongaflag.gif" ALT="Flag of Tonga" WIDTH=100></A>
<HR>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=450><tr>
<TD width 200><TD align=left>http://acij.uts.edu.au/cafepacific/resources/profiles/tonga.html
</table>
<HR>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 width=450><tr>
<TD width 200><TD align=left>
<P>
<Font size=6><A HREF="../david_prof.html"><B>Tonga</A></B></Font size=6>
<P>
<H4><IMG SRC="../../images/bullet.gif"> Go to <A HREF="#News media">News media</A></H4>
<P>
<Font size=3><B>Head of State:</B>King Taufa'ahau Tupou IV.
<BR>
<B>Head of Government:</B> Prime Minister Baron Vaea
<BR><B>Capital:</B>Nuku'alofa (on Tongatapu).
<BR><B>Official languages:</B> Tongan (English used in education and administration).
<BR><B>Currency:</B> Tongan pa'anga = 100 seniti
<BR><B>Area:</B> 748 sq km (170 islands).
<BR><B>Population:</B> 98 300 (1994 SPC est) -- <B>Tongatapu:</B> 63 614; Vava'u: 15 170.
<BR><B>Time: </B> + 1300 hours GMT.
<BR><B>Gross national product: </B> US$70m (1985).
<BR><B>GNP per capita: </B> US$730.
<BR><B>Aid: </B> A$13 million (1980); per capta A$134.
<BR><B>Literacy: </B> 78 per cent (UNESCO 1990).<P><IMG SRC="../../images/tongamap.gif" BORDER=2 ALT="Map of Tonga" WIDTH=250>
<BR><Font size=1>Map: Gemini News Service</Font size=1>
<P><B>Political system: </B> Tonga is governed by a hereditary monarch who appoints and chairs a Privy Council consisting of seven life ministers -- inclusing an executive prime minister -- and the governors of Ha'apai and Vava'u. A unicameral legislative council of 28 members meets annually but only nine of its places are filled by elected representatives of the commoners.
<P>
<B>Political parties:</B> Until 1994 there were no organised political parties, but the Pro-Democracy Movement, led by 'Akilisi Pohiva, won six out of the nine People's Representative seats in the February 1993 election. In late 1994 the movement formed the Democracy Party. On 19 September 1996 the kingdom was shaken when Pohiva, regarded as one of the leading whistleblowers of the South Pacific, and two editors of the Taimi 'o Tongan newspaper were jailed for 30 days for alleged contempt of parliament. The action drew wide international condemnation.
<P>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="News media">News media:</A></H3>
<B>Press:</B>
<UL><LI><B>Ko'e Kele'a: </B>Bimonthly; 5000; Tongan/English language; associated with Pro-Democracy Movement; Publisher/editor: 'Akilisi Pohiva. PO Box 956, Nuku'alofa. Tel: (676) 21215. A whistleblowing newsletter with critical analyses of Tongan political and current affairs.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.netstorage.com/kami/tonga/news/index.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/tonga_chronicle.gif" WIDTH=200>
<BR><B>Ko'e Kalonikali Tonga (Tonga Chronicle):</B></A> Weekly; 5000 Tongan; 1500 English;  Information Division, Kingdom of Tonga. Tungi Arcade, Suite 205, Taufa'ahau Rd, PO Box 197, Nuku'alofa. Tel: (676) 23302; Fax: (676) 23336. National and international news. Email: <A HREF="samt@gco.apana.org.au">samt@gco.apana.org.au</A>
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.netstorage.com/kami/tonga/matangi/index.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/matangilogo.jpg" WIDTH=200>
<BR><B>Matangi Tonga:</B></A> Bimonthly; English/Tongan language; 2000; Vava'u Press Ltd. Publisher/Editor: Pesi Fonua, co-editor: Mary Fonua. Haveluloto, PO Box 427, Nuku'alofa. Tel: (676) 23101; Fax: (676) 24749. National news magazine. Email: <A HREF="kami@netstorage.com">kami@netstorage.com</A>
<P>
<LI><B>Taimi 'o Tonga (Tongan Times):</B></A> Weekly; English/Tongan language; Lali Communications Ltd. Editor: Kalafi Moala. Siu'ilikutapu Rd, Kolomutu'a, PO Box 880, Nuku'alofa. Tel: (676) 23177; Fax (<I>Auckland main office</I>): (649) 579 1805. National and international news.</UL>
<P>
<B>Radio:</B>
<UL><LI><B>Radio Tonga:</B> State-run broadcaster; Tonga Broadcasting Commission. Two services: one Am and the other commercial FM. News director: Laumanu Petelo. PO Box 36, Nuku'alofa. Tel: (676) 23555; Fax: (676) 24417.
<P>
<LI><B>Tonga FM93:</B> United Christian Broadcasters. PO Box, 478 Nuku'alofa. Tel: (676) 23076; Fax: (676) 23076. 
<P></UL>
<B>Television:</B>
<UL><LI><B>Oceania Broadcasting Network Ltd:</B> PO Box 91, Nuku'alofa. Tel: (676) 23314; Fax: (676) 23658.
<P>
</UL>

<Font size=1> Copyright © 1996 David Robie and South Pacific Centre for Communication and Information in Development (SPCenCIID)</Font size=1>
<HR>
<A HREF="../david_prof.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/Nius.gif" height=27> Return to Nius country profiles index</A>
</P>
</TABLE>
