Media Centre</A><BR>
<IMG vspace=10 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<A HREF="../credit.html">Credits</A></B><BR></FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=10><P></TD>
<!--End Index Table-->

<!--Begin Body Table-->
<TD VALIGN=top WIDTH=370>

<!--Begin Heading Table-->
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=360 HEIGHT=162>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=15></TD>
<TD><A NAME="top"><IMG WIDTH=198 HEIGHT=90 SRC="../images/interbw75.gif"></A></TD>
<TD WIDTH=15></TD>
<TD><IMG WIDTH=105 HEIGHT=145  SRC="../images/logo75.gif"></TD>
<TD></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<!--End Heading Table-->

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=365 SRC="../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<!--Begin Body Table-->
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 WIDTH=360>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><P></TD>
<TD>
<CENTER>
<B><FONT SIZE="+2">Newsagency Reporting</FONT></B>
</CENTER>
<br><IMG vspace=2 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<FONT SIZE="+1">Section Four</FONT>
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
Not many Australian realise that the international news services like AP report every aspect of Australia.
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>	
Stories on Pauline Hanson and her attitude to race went to all 112 countries where AP news services are used. Add the Reuters and AFP subscribers and you can safely say there are few editors on the planet who didn't get the opportunity to publish it.
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>	
Treasurer Peter Costello's unguarded remarks in Washington about US interest rates hit more than 100,000 dealing screens around the world and caused a major flurry in the bond markets.
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>	
Few people are aware that general news filed by these agencies does not only go to newspapers, or radio and television stations. It also appears on screens around the world where decisions are
made that can effect stock markets and currency markets the world over.
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
Although the early AP was a much different organisation than the one today, the objectives have not greatly changed.
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
"My business is to communicate facts,": said Lawrence Gobright, who began reporting Washington news for AP in 1848, its first year of operation. 
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
"My instructions do not allow me to make any comments on the facts. My dispatches are sent to papers of all manner of politics. I therefore confine myself to what I consider legitimate news and try to be truthful and impartial." 
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
As communications makes our global reach much greater, it also increases the scrutiny of our work. Lawrence Gobright's dictum remains as true today as it was 148 years ago.
</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><br><IMG vspace=15 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br></TD>
