<IMG vspace=10 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<A HREF="../credit.html">Credits</A></B><BR></FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=10><P></TD>
<!--End Index Table-->

<!--Begin Body Table-->
<TD VALIGN=top WIDTH=370>

<!--Begin Heading Table-->
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=360 HEIGHT=162>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=15></TD>
<TD><A NAME="top"><IMG WIDTH=198 HEIGHT=90 SRC="../images/interbw75.gif"></A></TD>
<TD WIDTH=15></TD>
<TD><IMG WIDTH=105 HEIGHT=145  SRC="../images/logo75.gif"></TD>
<TD></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<!--End Heading Table-->

<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<IMG height=2 width=365 SRC="../resources/dot_peri.gif"><br>
<IMG vspace=5 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>

<!--Begin Body Table-->
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 WIDTH=360>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><P></TD>
<TD>
<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE="+2">Newsagencies in Transition</FONT></B></CENTER>
<br><IMG vspace=2 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
<FONT SIZE="+1">Section Four</FONT>
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>
Journalism as we know it is facing a big ethical challenge. Now we are experiencing a "fast food" era of journalism. Competition has never been so fierce to serve the ever hungry news consumer. Today the definition of a good reports is a report that comes first. In Thailand, criminal suspects have been known to demand money as TV stations scrambled to be the first to interview them.
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>	
One English-language newspaper in my country has adjusted its writing style. Stories have been shortened and the language simplified to allow readers to absorb news more quickly. We haven't done that we may be forced to do so one day.
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>	
Media organisations will have more intertwined business interests. There will be continuous expansions and frequent mergers. But as media empires grow and become more powerful all over the world, how they will treat small voices of unorganised dissident or individuals is a major question.
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>	
The new generation of news organisations will contain broadcast, telephone, satellite and fibre optics. This will subject them to government regulation or control. My newspaper has ventured into TV and radio businesses and we are calling ourselves a multimedia group. Clashes with the government over how to handle an issue have become increasingly common.
<br><IMG vspace=3 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br>	
These are the challenges facing journalists all over the world. We are required to be fast, fair and objective at the same time. We have to cope with changing habit of news consumers while world's problems of suffering, poverty, oppression remain unchanged. The future is full of hope, but it will test journalists' ability to adjust themselves.
</TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=20><br><IMG vspace=15 hspace=0 SRC="../resources/dot_clear.gif"><br></TD>
