<HTML>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TITLE>Media Magazine</TITLE>
<CENTER>
<A NAME="top"></A>
<IMG WIDTH=350 ALIGN=CENTRE HEIGHT=218 SRC="../images/mm.title.jpg">
<BR>
<IMG WIDTH=450 ALIGN=CENTRE HEIGHT=50 SRC="../images/banner.about.jpg">
</CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<I>Media Magazine</I> is the longest running media and communications program in Australia and the longest running national community radio program in Australia.  Now seventeen years old, <I>Media Magazine</I> is produced at 2SER-FM, a community radio station  owned by the University of Technology, Sydney and Macquarie University.  Each week the program is broadcast by more than twenty community radio stations around Australia.  It is also available for <a href="../buy/education.html">purchase as an educational resource</a>. 
<BR><BR>

Each weekly program runs for thirty minutes and the programs contain a variety of news, interviews, features and documentaries.  Our broad aim is to provide independent, critical and accessible analysis of media and communications issues, paying special attention to community media.  Really keen people might want to read the <I>Media Magazine</I> <a href="./aims.html">aims and objectives.</a>
<BR><BR>
The program is currently produced by <a href=mailto:radio.2ser-fm@uts.edu.au>Michael Dwyer.</a>  Past producers form a distinguished list of journalists, academics and people still working in community broadcasting.
<BR><BR>
You can also read more about <a href="../history/index.html">the history of <I>Media Magazine</I>. </a>
<BR><BR>
The project receives funding from the Australian Film Commission and the Community Broadcasting Foundation.
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
