<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TITLE>Media Magazine</TITLE>
<CENTER>
<A NAME="top"></A>
<IMG WIDTH=350 ALIGN=CENTRE HEIGHT=218 SRC="../images/mm.title.jpg">
<BR>
<IMG WIDTH=450 ALIGN=CENTRE HEIGHT=50 SRC="../images/banner.buy.jpg">
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<H3><I>Media Magazine</I> as an educational resource</H3>
</CENTER>
<BR>
Each week <I>Media Magazine</I> provides an unique insight on the media and communications sector in Australia.  From our position in community media we give no favours and over the last sventeen years the program has developed a reputation for indepedent analysis. 
<BR><BR>
Debate about media and communications is often peppered with jargon, acronyms and other barriers to understanding.  At <I>Media Magazine</I> we attempt to cut through that approach and provide anlaysis which is accessible while still being of a high standard.  
<BR><BR>
And while the program approaches issues from a variety of perspectives - political, technological, aesthetic, economic, cultural - we try to emphasise the role of communication as it impacts on people's lives.  Our programs tend to give more weight to consumer and community issues than most of our competitors.  
<BR><BR>
For these and many more reasons we belive <I>Media Magazine</I> to be a highly useful addition to the resources available to media and communications students.  We'd ask you to consider recommending your students listen to <I>Media Magazine</I> if a community radio station broadcasts the program <a href="../broadcast/index.html">in your area</a>.  
<BR><BR>
If not, please lobby your local station or consider <a href="../buy/index.html">purchasing a subscription to <I>Media Magazine</I> </a>for your school, department or university library.

<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<img width=223 height=31 src="../images/mm.flat.
bottom.banner.jpg">
