<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>THE GEORGE MUNSTER AWARD FOR FREELANCE JOURNALISM</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=475><tr>
<td width=30><BR></td>
<td width=445>
<H1><CENTER>THE GEORGE MUNSTER AWARD FOR FREELANCE JOURNALISM</CENTER></H1>


<H2>Guidelines for the 1996 Award</H2>


<H3>About George Munster</H3>

George Munster was a co-founder of the <B>Nation</B>, a fortnightly journal (later to become <B>Nation Review</B>), and a freelance editor, journalist and writer of books. He later became an editor with Angus and Robertson Publishers and reverted to freelance work both as a journalist and book writer.<P>

When George's book <B>Rupert Murdoch:  A Paper Prince</B> was launched in October 1985, a little over a year after his death, a number of his friends decided to commemorate his life and the outstanding contribution he made to journalism by instituting an annual award to a freelance journalist.<P>

<H3>The Award</H3><P>

The award is for the best article or series of articles in the print media in the twelve months to 31 July 1996 OR the best program or series of programs on radio in the twelve months prior to 31 July 1996. Applicants must have been ordinarily resident in Australia for no less than twelve months prior to 31 July 1996.<P>

<B>Closing Date:</B>   Applications must be received by 14 October 1996.<BR>
<B>Award:</B>   $1,000<P>

A "freelance journalist" for the purposes of this Award is a person who was not a full-time employee of the media at the time that the submitted material was published or broadcast. Persons who were tenured academics during the course of the twelve months to 31 July 1996 are not eligible to apply.<BR>

Applicants must forward an Application Form and it must be accompanied by FOUR COPIES of the article/s in the print media, or by FOUR COPIES of relevant tapes and transcripts in the case of radio applications. <P>

Applicants may apply directly, or may be nominated by other people, including the management and editors of the newspapers, magazines and radio stations.<P>

The judges in their discretion may make the Award to a person who has not been nominated or who has not applied - and they may make the Award either for a specific work or for the journalist's general contribution to freelance journalism. <P>

The Award will be made to the applicant whose material is considered by the judges to be most in the spirit of the journalism of George Munster himself, which was characterised by independence, integrity, accuracy and lucid and elegant prose.<P>

The Award Presentation will be made in November 1996.<P>

Application forms are available from the Australian Centre for Independent Journalism.<P>

George Munster Award for Freelance Journalism,<BR>
c/- Australian Centre for Independent Journalism,<BR>
University of Technology, Sydney,<BR>
PO Box 123, Broadway  NSW  2007.<BR>
Phone  (02) 9514 2488<BR>
Web  <A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/">http://acij.uts.edu.au/</A>
</td></tr></table>

