<TITLE>Media Magazine</TITLE>
<A NAME="top"></A>
<CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=350 ALIGN=CENTRE HEIGHT=218 SRC="../images/mm.title.jpg">
<BR>
<IMG WIDTH=450 ALIGN=CENTRE HEIGHT=50 SRC="../images/banner.about.jpg">
</CENTER>
<BR><BR>
<H2>AIMS AND OBJECTIVES</H2>

The <I>Media Magazine</I> project has a clear set of aims and objectives.  They identify the role of the project within a media environment that is an uneven playing field.  Each year we strive to meet these aims and objectives in new and innovative ways.
<BR><BR>
<B>Aims</B>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>To produce a national weekly half-hour program on media and communications
<BR><BR>
<LI>To stimulate critical reflection on the role and form of community media 
<BR><BR>
<LI>To encourage critical analysis of the media through educational and stimulating programming
	<BR><BR>
<LI>To provide specialist knowledge of the area in an accessible format
	<BR><BR>
<LI>To encourage a broad range of contributors to the program especially from outside Sydney and Melbourne
	<BR><BR>
<LI>To present a community-focused perspective on issues in the media by seeking to represent communities which may not have easy access to the media
</UL>
<BR>
<B>Objectives</B><BR>
<UL>
<LI>Develop critical understandings of the media and issues relevant to it by providing information and lively debate
	<BR><BR>
<LI>Present a well-informed program of a high technical standard, making use of a diversity of people and resources for program ideas in a range of radio formats
	<BR><BR>
<LI>Present information in an accessible form, avoiding unnecessary jargon, giving examples and explaining issues as clearly as possible.
	<BR><BR>
<LI>Ensure that the program is responsive to its audience by seeking feedback wherever possible
</UL>
<BR>
