<head><title> Pacific Media Watch: View</title></head>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<HR>
<TD width=475 align=left>
<IMG SRC="../images/pmwlogo.gif" WIDTH=100> <Font size=6>Pacific Media Watch</Font 6>
<h1>Viewpoint: 'Media suppression evil'</h1>
<Font size=3><B>PMW08: Post-Courier (PNG): 14 November 1996
<P>
Title -- 337 MEDIA: Viewpoint condemns draft media law
Date -- 14 November 1996
Byline -- Morris Roy Toragaia
Origin -- Pacific Media Watch
Source -- Post-Courier (PNG), 14/11/96
Copyright -- Post-Courier
Status -- Unabridged
<P>
<HR>
<P>
Viewpoint by Morris Roy Toragaia (Lae, Morobe Province)</B><BR>
Anyone who suppresses democracy has an evil motive - CRC's obsession to control to media is no exception.
<P>
Their motive is to prevent the media from exposing the wrongs and evil doings
of the government, which means the population will be fed with false and
misleading information.
<P>
As educated Papua New Guineans, we must ask ourselves, are we heading for a
dictatorship or what ? We are now witnessing the truths and realities unfolding before our eyes. CRC is headed and controlled by politicians. Ben Micah and his cohorts won't feel the negative impact of their decisions as they are very, very comfortable and living in paradise. 
<P>
What about us the three-and-a-half million people, especially our brothers and sisters that live in villages and remote inlands, making up about 80 per cent of the population?
<P>
My parents used to say to me: "Why worry if you have nothing to hide ?" Here we see CRC worrying. Their mission statement seems to be: "Cling on to power at any cost." 
<P>
Sadly, we the people will suffer the consequences. They no longer care about the suffering, pain and misery they have bestowed upon us. We must not let this group continue insulting the intelligence of the majority.
<P>
For our future generations, I urge all educated citizens to be critical and
question the CRC ploy. I urge all politicians to vote from their hearts and
with conscience. Papua New Guinea is our motherland .... let us prevent any
ill-concieved fantasies that will erode or is now eroding the fabric of our
society. 
<P>
Let demcracy prevail! Let media freedom prevail! God save Papua New Guinea.<BR>
