<TITLE>Media Magazine - Community Media in Australia</TITLE>
<A NAME="top"></A>
<CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=350 ALIGN=CENTRE HEIGHT=218 SRC="../images/mm.title.jpg">
<BR>
<IMG WIDTH=450 ALIGN=CENTRE HEIGHT=50 SRC="../images/banner.commedia.jpg">
</CENTER>

<BR>
<BR>
<H2>Sixth Channel Inquiry</H2>
<BR>
This inquiry was set up to decide what permanent use should be allowed for the final free-to-air terrestrial television channel available across Australia.
<BR><BR>
Since 1992 Community Television groups have been licensed to conduct test transmissions on the sixth channel in all state capitals and some regional areas.  This will end before mid 1997.  Apart from continued use by community television other potential uses being considered include an arts channel, a childrens channel, a womens channel and a variety of non-broadcast uses.  The inquiry is being conducted by the Australian broadcasting Authority who are required to report to the Minister for Communications and the Arts by February 1997.
<BR><BR>
This page provides links to many relevant sites - please provide details of any other relevant sites.
<BR><BR>
<UL>
<LI><a href="http://www.dca.gov.au/mediarel/sixthchl.html">Department of Communications and the Arts media release announcing the inquiry</a>
<BR><BR>
<LI><a href="http://www.dca.gov.au/aba/6chhome.htm">Australian Broadcasting Authority Sixth Channel Inquiry Home Page</a>
<BR><BR>Contains links to terms of reference, issues paper, submissions received and much much more.
<BR><BR>
<LI><a href="http://www.dca.gov.au/aba/6comm.htm">Submissions to the inquiry on community use of the sixth channel</a>
<BR><BR>
<LI><a href="http://www.scu.edu.au/cbaa/tvlist.html">List of community television members of the CBAA</a>
</UL>
<BR>
<BR>


