<HTML> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" alink="#8c7853" vlink="#006600">
<HEAD><TITLE>Issue 1, Hill</TITLE></HEAD> 
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=390 HEIGHT=80 ALT="Uni Tavur" ALIGN=TOP SRC="UniT_mast.gif"></CENTER>

<hr>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
<TD width= 200></TD><td align =left> http://acij.uts.edu.au/UniTavur/UniT_196_Hill.html</td><tr>
</table>
<hr>

<IMG alt=UniTavur Icon BORDER =0 ALIGN=BASELINE WIDTH=28 HEIGHT=30 SRC="Unit_slug.gif"><Font size= 5> 
Hills pledges new life for university <font size= 3><p>

<strong> Lawrence Fong & Elizabeth Solomon</strong><p>



<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=475> <TD width= 475  align =left>

The new University of Papua New Guinea Vice-Chancellor, Dr Rodney Hills, has
vowed to sweep aside crime, violence and security problems on campus and to
restore the institution's reputation.<P> </td></tr>
</table>

<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=475>
<td width =290 align left> And he appealed to students and staff to help him rebuild campus life by taking
part in social activities to improve "better understanding" of one another.  He
said  :  "You must try to work together so that you develop a happy environment." <p>

Speaking to student journalists in the new Uni Tavur  newsroom this week, Dr
Hills said he had been to many  universities throughout the world - including
Princeton and Harvard in the United States - before coming to PNG. <P>

Comparing  UPNG with other universities, Dr Hills said one of the ingredients
lacking at Waigani campus was a friendly working relationship between students
and staff.<P>

"In many other universities, students feel comfortable discussing anything with
their lecturers - be it a problem or an exchange of ideas on any issue," he
said.<P></TD>

<td align=center> <IMG  alt= "Dr.Rodney Hill." SRC= "UT-Hill.jpg"></td><tr>

</table>


<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=475> <TD width= 475  align =left>
Dr Hills called for a series of evening seminars and lectures where students
could come together and participate in lively discussions.<P>

He gave an example where staff and students could produce drama and draw crowds
back to campus.<P>

Dr Hills also stressed support for freedom of the press.<P>
"I believe in freedom of the press. However, the press should be accurate," he
said.<P>

Training of journalists was important and reporters should be aiming for
responsibility and accuracy in their careers.<P>

"Crime and violence on campus are often associated with alcohol and drugs and I
want these out of the way to achieve a good university lifestyle," Dr Hills
said.<P>

Since taking office six weeks ago, he has made several bold moves to tackle
violence problems, including introducing better campus lighting. <P>

</td></tr>
</table>



