<IMG alt=UniTavur Icon BORDER =0 ALIGN=BASELINE WIDTH=28 HEIGHT=30 SRC="http://acij.uts.edu.au/UniTavur/Unit_slug.gif"><Font size= 5> 

UNI TAVUR ON LEAVE.<font size=3><p>

<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=475> <TD width= 475  align=left>
<P>
Uni Tavur is taking a well-earned break from publishing during the second semester 1996. Our print lecturer, <A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/PJR/david.html">David Robie</A>, is on research leave and budget cuts for the university have had an impact. Regular advertisers and subscribers will be given a credit for the semester. We'll be back as usual next year.
<P>
But we haven't shut down completely for the semester. A leaner A4 newsletter version of the paper, <A HREF="UniT_toktok.html">Uni Tavur Toktok</A>, is being produced by the students and <I>Post-Courier</I> subeditor Francis Uliau instead. With help from the <A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/">Australian Centre for Independent Journalism</A> on this website, this electronic newspaper will be updated. Watch also for Ita Diba and <A HREF="http://acij.uts.edu.au/PJR/index.html">Pacific Journalism Review</A> on the Web -- or try our <A HREF="http://www.pactok.net/docs/nius">Papua Niugini Nius</A> site.

</TABLE>

</td><tr>

