<HTML>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TITLE>Media Magazine - Program 2/96</TITLE>
<A NAME="top"></A>
<BR>
<BR>
<img width=115 align=left height=80 src="cueimage/mm.Australia.
6.gif"><BR>
<H2>MEDIA MAGAZINE CUE SHEET <BR>
Program 2/96 <BR>
ComRadSat TX 8/2/96</H2>
</center>
<BR><BR>
<table>
<td>Program In</td><td><B>theme</B></td><td>Last Words At</td><td><B>26:20</B></td><tr>
<td>Program Out</td><td><B>theme</B></td><td>Total Duration</td><td><B>27:40</B></td>
</table>
<BR><BR>

<B>Item One - Consumers Telecommunications Network on the Election and the Year Ahead</B><BR><BR>

Telecommunications has continued to make news in week two of the Federal Election campaign.  Despite the ALP and Democrats agreeing to block the part sale of Telstra in the Senate,  the Coalition was still claiming that the sale would go ahead and would pay for their environmental policy.  The Comsumers Telecommunications Network is a national policy and lobby group for telecommunications consumers.  Michael Dwyer asked Acting Director Gerard Goggin for his comments on the year ahead, on the election and on the sale of Telstra ...
<BR><BR>
<table>
<td>in</td><td>"Well we've raised...</td><tr>
<td>out</td><td>...telecommunications providers."</td><tr>
<td>duration</td><td>7:15</td><tr>
<td>talent</td><td>Acting Director - Consumers Telecommunications Network, Gerard Goggin</td>
 </table>
<BR><BR>
<B>Item Two	-	AUSTEL report on telecommunications national code released</B>
<BR><BR>
Many residents and councils are up in arms over optical fibre networks and mobile phone towers in their streets.  Under pressure to build-up their customer bases, companies like Optus, Vodafone and Telstra are rapidly expanding their communications infrastructure.  The Federal Government has made this building program easier by exempting the companies from the usual local planning procedures.  Angry at the powers given to telecommunications companies, residents and councils have conducted many protests and have taken their claims to the courts.  This backlash led to a review of the planning exemptions set out in the Telecommunications National Code.  Michael Dwyer asked General Manager of  at AUSTEL John Haydon what were the main recommendations of the review...<BR><BR>

<table>
<td>in</td><td>"The report was a fairly...</td><tr>
<td>out</td><td>...part in the process."</td><tr>
<td>duration</td><td>2:25</td><tr>
<td>talent</td><td>General Manager of Industry Affairs at AUSTEL - John Haydon</td>
</table>
<BR><BR>

<B>Item Three	-	Media Reporting of Indigenous Issue</B>s <BR><BR>

The standard of media reporting of indigenous issues has long been of concern.  Having just passed through the International Year for Tolerance you might be excused for imagining things would change.  Not according to 
Dr Michael Meadows, Senior Lecturer in Print and Broadcast Journalism at Griffith University.  He argues that good journalism requires a dialogue between the reporter and the subject - something he doesn't see happening in the reporting of indigenous issues. So what is the importance of this dialogue...
<BR><BR>
<table>
<td>in</td><td>"I think it's the fact that...</td><tr>
<td>out</td><td>...to achieve that I guess."</td><tr>
<td>duration</td><td>8:00</td><tr>
<td>talent</td><td>Senior Lecturer in Print and Broadcast Journalism at Griffith University - Dr Michael Meadows</td>
 </table>
<BR><BR>
<B>Item Four	-	Launch of Indigenous CD-ROM and Internet Site</B>
<BR><BR>
Ever wanted to read the Mabo judgement for yourself?  Along with important reports such as the Royal Commission into Aboriginal Deaths in Custody, the judgement is now available on CD-ROM and on the internet.  The project was co-ordinated by the Council for Aboriginal Reconciliation -  Deputy Chair of the Council Ian Viner QC told Michael Dwyer about the information available...
<BR><BR>
<table>
<td>in</td><td>"Well it's a huge range...</td><tr>
<td>out</td><td>...justice, equity and reconciliation."</td><tr>
<td>duration</td><td>2:35</td><tr>
<td>talent</td><td>Deputy Chair of the Council for Aboriginal Reconciliation - Ian Viner QC</td>
 </table><BR><BR><BR>




<B>APRA DETAILS AVAILABLE ON REQUEST</B>

<BR>
<BR>
<img width=223 height=31 src="cueimage/mm.flat.
