<HTML>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TITLE>Media Magazine - Program 20/96</TITLE>
<A NAME="top"></A>
<BR>
<BR>
<img width=115 align=left height=80 src="cueimage/mm.Australia.
6.gif"><BR>
<H2>MEDIA MAGAZINE CUE SHEET <BR>
Program 20/96 <BR>
ComRadSat TX 13/6/96</H2>
</center>
<BR><BR>
<table>
<td>Program In</td><td><B>theme</B></td><td>Last Words At</td><td><B>26:47</B></td><tr>
<td>Program Out</td><td><B>theme</B></td><td>Total Duration</td><td><B>28:00</B></td>
</table>
<BR><BR>
<B>Item One		New Staff Elected Director at the ABC</B>
<BR>
Kirsten Garrett is the newly elected Staff Elected Director at the Australian Broadcasting Corporation. The ABC has a been a hotbed of controversy for many months with prospective funding cuts and job losses looming.  Media Magazine took this opportunity to speak with Kirsten Garrett about ABC management and funding.  Michael Dwyer asked her whether the current public criticism being levelled between the government, current management and former management was at all productive...
<BR><BR>
<table>
<td>in</td><td>"I think that it's entirely...</td><tr>
<td>out</td><td>...what are almost ashes."</td><tr>
<td>duration</td><td>9:16</td><tr>
<td>talent</td><td>Staff Elected Director at the Australian Broadcasting Corporation -  Kirsten Garrett</td>
 </table>
<BR>
<B>Item Two		Independent Broadcasting in Serbia</B>
<BR><BR>

<I>Zombietown</I> is the name of a documentary on B92 - an independent radio station and television production house in Belgrade.   B92 is one of a very few non-government media organisations in Serbia and it is currently operating without any formal license.  As well as offering rare independent media coverage, B92 offers a space for young people and for artists to meet and begin to rebuild cultural life in Serbia and the war ravaged countries of the former Yugoslavia..  In this report Elisia Yeo speaks to Marc Hawker, Director of Zombietown and Michael Dwyer speaks to Ksenja Stasinovic, Head of Television Production at B92 ...
<BR><BR>
<table>
<td>in</td><td>Audio grab from B92 ...</td><tr>
<td>out</td><td>... frequency to broadcast the program."</td><tr>
<td>duration</td><td>6:30</td><tr>
<td>talent</td><td>Director of <I>Zombietown</I>, Marc Hawker<BR>
		Head of Television Production at B92, Ksenja Stasinovic</td>
 </table>
<BR>

<B>Item Three		U.S. Courts reject Communications Decency Act</B>
<BR><BR>

In what was a major victory for  internet activists, a U.S. court has  declared that the Communications Decency Act is unconstitutional.   The Act attempted to ban so-called indecent material from the Internet.  Many internet users in the United States and around the world have been fighting a campaign to have the Act repealed.  Shortly after the decision was announced I spoke to from the Electronic Freedom Foundation in the United States ...
<BR><BR>
<table>
<td>in</td><td>"See, we filed suit with...</td><tr>
<td>out</td><td>... and one in San Francisco."</td><tr>
<td>duration</td><td>5:04</td><tr>
<td>talent</td><td>Representative of the United States Electronic Freedom Foundation - Stanton McAndlis</td>
 </table>
<BR><BR>
<CENTER>
<B>APRA DETAILS AVAILABLE ON REQUEST</B>
</CENTER>
<BR><BR><BR>


