<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>CAET Home Page</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="logo.gif" ALT="IAMS" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=100 ALIGN=ABSCENTER>
</P></CENTER>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><B>Center for Applied <BR>
Environmental Technologies</B></H1>

<P><I>Do you have excessive manufacturing waste? </I></P>

<P><I>Do you have high energy bills? </I></P>

<P><I>Do you need help following through on that &quot;great idea&quot;?
</I></P>

<P><I>Do you need a fresh perspective? </I></P>

<P><I>Do you need help teaching your staff problem-solving skills?</I>
</P>

<H4>IAMS CAET can help you.</H4>

<P><B>IAMS Center for Applied Environmental Technologies</B> (CAET) is
a not-for profit organization organized to assist manufacturers with reducing
manufacturing costs and regulatory burden. </P>

<P>Our expert staff has technical knowledge and hands-on experience to
quickly assess your manufacturing operations and make recommendations that
go right ot your bottom line. </P>

<P>We're different from other consultants because our job is to save your
company money. Our mission, to: </P>

<UL>
<LI>improve your financial performance, </LI>

<LI>supply expertise and training to reduce your manufacturing costs and
</LI>

<LI>reduce your regulatory burden,</LI>
</UL>

<P>is only fulfilled when your company increases manufacturing yield and
reduces overall unit costs. 
<HR></P>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="#Manufacturing assessments">Manufacturing Assessments</A></H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="#Environmental hotline">Environmental Hotline</A></H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="#Training">Training</A></H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="#CAET Publications">CAET Publications</A></H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="#Environmental Networking Groups">Environmental
Networking Groups</A></H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="#CAET Staff">CAET Staff</A></H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="#Environmental Events Calendar">Environmental
Events Calendar</A></H3>

<H2>
<HR WIDTH="100%"><A NAME="Manufacturing assessments"></A><IMG SRC="10.gif" HEIGHT=26 WIDTH=26 ALIGN=TOP><B>Manufacturing
Assessments</B></H2>

<UL>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.iams.org/outreach/energy.htm"><IMG SRC="file:///W|/htdocs/caet/grnball.gif" BORDER=0 " HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 ALIGN=TOP></A><A HREF="http://www.iams.org/outreach/energy.htm">
<B>Energy Reduction</B></A> </DT>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.iams.org/outreach/waste.htm"><IMG SRC="grnball.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 ALIGN=TOP></A><B><A HREF="http://www.iams.org/outreach/waste.htm">Waste
Reduction<BR>
<A HREF="faq.htm"><IMG SRC="file:///W|/htdocs/caet/grnball.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 ALIGN=TOP></A></A><A HREF="faq.htm">Frequently
Asked Questions about Assessments</A></B></DT>
</UL>

<UL>
<UL>
<P>As a result of CAET's services, an Ohio company is saving $10,000 a
month; another firm has eliminated hazardous wastes entirely; a third has
eliminated the need for air permits; and a Cincinnati company can use non-recyclable
waste paper as boiler fuel to eliminate the 200 tons of annual solid waste
going into the landfill.</P>

<P>Several years ago, IAMS was able to assist a local company, <A HREF="http://pages.prodigy.com/L/P/O/lpco/index.htm">Leonhardt
Plating</A> reduce their waste. Leonhardt Plating is a Cincinnati, family-owned
and operated job-shop electroplating business. The 20 company employees
provide a variety of metal finishing services including polishing, buffing,
electroless nickel plating, nickel and chrom electroplating and electropolishing.</P>

<P>IAMS performed a waste minimization assessment for Leonhardt Plating
and by implementing IAMS recommendations, Leonhardt's process water consumption
dropped from 500 thousand gallons per month to around 160 thousand gallons
per month saving them $5,000 annually!</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.iams.org/caet/leonhard.htm">Leonhardt Case Study</A></P>
</UL>
</UL>

<P>
<HR><BR>
</P>

<H2><A NAME="Environmental hotline"></A><IMG SRC="10.gif" HEIGHT=26 WIDTH=26 ALIGN=TOP><B>Environmental
Hotline</B></H2>

<UL>
<P>Troubleshooting answers to difficult questions on company waste problems
and pollution prevention concerns<B>--(513) 948-2050 or (800) 345-4482</B></P>
</UL>

<P>
<HR></P>

<H2><A NAME="Training"></A><IMG SRC="10.gif" HEIGHT=26 WIDTH=26 ALIGN=TOP><B>Training</B></H2>

<UL>
<P>CAET offers a variety of environmental training opportunities. Training
is available both on-site at the Institute of Advanced Manufacturing Sciences
or at convenient locations throughout the State of Ohio. Training is often
available at no charge to participants through the generous support of
various sponsoring organizations. </P>

<UL>
<LI><B>&quot;Pollution Prevention Basics&quot;</B> is generally a one to
two hour presentation which provides an introduction to the pollution prevention
(P2) concept, an awareness of P2 benefits, the regulatory framework for
waste minimization, identification of the various opportunities for implementation,
and a discussion of state and federal pollution prevention resources. The
training can be expanded to a half day seminar through the incorporation
of pollution prevention case studies.</LI>
</UL>

<UL>
<LI><B>&quot;Lowering Costs Through Waste Reduction&quot;</B> is a half
or full day workshop focussing on the means of minimizing business costs
through waste reduction. Participants learn how to organize a Waste Minimization
Team, understand the brainstorming process, develop process flow diagrams,
conduct facility waste assessments, and develop and implement a Pollution
Prevention Plan. Case studies are also featured at the workshop through
industrial panel presentations and participants receive information on
industry-specific technical and financial resources. </LI>
</UL>

<UL>
<LI><B>&quot;Environmental Awareness Training&quot;</B> is a full day seminar
that provides a general introduction to environmental issues and then a
more comprehensive overview of specific environmental regulations. The
company or organization requesting the seminar selects the regulations
to be addressed during the day-long course. The intent of the effort is
to familiarize employees with the policies that are related to their work
place and to help them gain an understanding of the role they play in ensuring
policy compliance and waste reduction.</LI>
</UL>

<P>For additional information on the above listed events and other environmental
training opportunities, please contact <A HREF="mailto:gillens@iams.org">gillens@iams.org</A></P>

<DT><A HREF="http://www.iams.org/events/webevent.htm"><IMG SRC="grnball.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 ALIGN=TOP></A><A HREF="http://www.iams.org/events/webevent.htm">
<B>IAMS Seminars</B></A> provides the current training program schedule
and event registration.</DT>
</UL>

<P>
<HR></P>

<H2><A NAME="CAET Publications"></A><IMG SRC="10.gif" HEIGHT=26 WIDTH=26 ALIGN=TOP><B>CAET
Publications</B><IMG SRC="books.gif" HEIGHT=65 WIDTH=60 ALIGN=TOP></H2>

<UL>
<DT><IMG SRC="grnball.gif" HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 ALIGN=TOP> <B>Metal Fabrication
Industry</B> </DT>

<UL>
<P><B><I>Shop Guide to Reduce the Waste of Metalworking Fluids</I></B>
<BR>
The purpose of this manual is to provide practical methods of reducing
coolant and lubricant wastes. Extensive progress has been made in recent
years in improving metalworking and fabrication processes, as regulations
regarding the discharges into the environment have become more stringent.
Many companies find they benefit from the guidelines in this manual in
the following ways:</P>

<UL>
<LI>Cost reduction by waste minimization</LI>

<LI>Decrease waste disposal costs and liability by recycling and reuse
of metalworking fluids</LI>

<LI>Reduce downtime and improve productivity</LI>

<LI>Improve quality, repeatability and costs of the products they manufacture</LI>
</UL>

<P>This manual will prove useful for companies involved in grinding, metal
removal and forming which may include: Broaching, Threading, Forming, Turning,
Tapping, Stamping, Milling, Drilling, Drawing.</P>

<P><A HREF="ftp://ftp.iams.org/pub/caet/fluids.pdf">Download Adobe Acrobat
version - 669 k</A></P>

<P><A HREF="ftp://ftp.iams.org/pub/caet/fluids.zip">Download Adobe Acrobat
version (zipped) - 459 k</A></P>

<P><BR>
<B><I>Shop Guide to Reduce Wastewater from the Machining and Metal Fabrication
Industry</I></B> <BR>
This manual covers a broad range of wastewater discharge areas in a metalworking
plant. Ideally, this manual provides methods in which manufacturers can
obtain zero wastewater discharge. Main topic areas include: aqueous-based
cleaners, cooling water, rinse operations, plant clean-up, conservation
of water techniques, deburring and mass finishing, cutting and blasting
operations, air pollution control equipment and wastewater treatment systems
buyer's guide.</P>

<P><A HREF="ftp://ftp.iams.org/pub/caet/wastewtr.pdf">Download Adobe Acrobat
version - 840 k</A></P>

<P><A HREF="ftp://ftp.iams.org/pub/caet/wastewtr.zip">Download Adobe Acrobat
version (zipped) - 533 k</A></P>

<P>If you'd like to receive the manuals by mail, please e-mail Trent Wall:
<A HREF="mailto:wall@iams.org">wall@iams.org</A> . <B>There is a $10 shipping
and handling charge</B>.</P>
</UL>

<DT><IMG SRC="grnball.gif" HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 ALIGN=TOP> <B>Electroplating
Industry</B> </DT>

<UL>
<P><B><I><A HREF="http://www.iams.org/p2irisde/metalfin.htm">Now available
for download: A Pollution Prevention Resource Manual for Metal Finishers<BR>
</A></I></B>(Also available by calling 1-800-345-4482 or 513-948-2026)</P>
</UL>

<DT><IMG SRC="grnball.gif" HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 ALIGN=TOP> <B>Printing Industry</B>
</DT>

<UL>
<DT><IMG SRC="new.gif" HEIGHT=12 WIDTH=31>Printing (coming Spring 1997)
</DT>
</UL>
</UL>

<P><BR>

