<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Edison Home Page</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Glenn Benz, 15-Jan-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/logo.gif" ALT="IAMS" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE">
<H1>OTHER EDISON CENTERS</H1></CENTER>

<HR>

<H2>Link to the <A HREF="http://www.ohio.gov">Ohio Department of Development</A> web site and the <A HREF="http://www.ohiobiz.com">Ohio Business</A> web site </H2>

<HR>
<h3><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/blueball.gif" ALT="NEW" ALIGN="TOP">
Edison BioTechnology Center</h3></P>

<P>Since its founding in 1987, the Edison BioTechnology
Center (EBTC) has become the premier advocate for Ohio's biotech/biomed
industry.</P>
<P>EBTC uses its extensive resource network as well as its staff expertise in law, FDA regulation, marketing and management to help emerging companies address specific business issues.  By serving as a source of practical assistance to these companies, EBTC is also expanding its role as an information clearinghouse.</P>

Edison Bio Technology Center
<br>11000Cedar Avenue
<br>Cleveland, OHIO  44106
<br>(216) 229-0400  FAX (216) 229-7323


<HR>
<A HREF="http://www.ohiou.edu/ictto/ebi.html">
<H3><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/blueball.gif" ALT="NEW" ALIGN="TOP">
Ohio University Edison BioTechnology Center</H3></A>

<P>The Ohio University Edison Biotechnology Institute is a cost-effective alternative in meeting the R&D needs of
both established and new companies. The Institute offers a broad range of contract research, including but not
limited to: </P>
<ul>
 <li>    Development of gene delivery systems 
 <li>    Development of gene expression analysis systems 
 <li>    Applications of embryology and cell/tissue culture science 
 <li>    Development of animal models for pharmaceutical evaluation 
 <li>    Development of improved agricultural species 
 <li>    Development of protien and other biopolymer based pharmaceuticals 
 <li>    Development of systems for human gene therapy 
</ul>
</P>
<HR>
<H3><A HREF="http://www.camp.org">
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/blueball.gif" ALT="NEW" ALIGN="TOP">
Cleveland Advanced Manufacturing Program</A></h3>

<P>Founded in 1984, CAMP is a not-for-profit economic development organization funded through Ohio's Thomas Edison Program, the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) , the Department of Defense (DoD) and other public and private sources. CAMP helps small-and medium-size manufacturing firms improve their global competitiveness through technology research, development, deployment and training.
</P>

<HR>
<h3><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/blueball.gif" ALT="NEW" ALIGN="TOP">
Edison Industrial Systems Center</h3></P>

<P>Through its partnerships with area industry,
universities and economic development agencies, the Edison Industrial
Systems Center has quickly become the focus for technology advancement
in Northwest Ohio.</P>

<HR>
<h3><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/blueball.gif" ALT="NEW" ALIGN="TOP">
Edison Materials Technology Center</H3>

<P>High quality materials and processing methods
are critical to the performance of all engineered products. The Edison
Materials Technology Center is responding to these needs with solutions
to industry's problems through special services, application of existing
technology and advanced technology development projects in industrial
materials and materials processing.</P>

<HR>
<h3>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/blueball.gif" ALT="NEW" ALIGN="TOP">
<A HREF="http://www.expert-market.com/otnet/epic.html">Edison Polymer Innovation Corporation</a></h3>

<P>Located in the Akron/Cleveland industrial
corridor known as "Polymer Valley," the Edison Polymer Innovation
Corporation is a member- driven organization which provides technical
resources to help polymer-related companies grow and prosper.</P>

<HR>
<H3><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/blueball.gif" ALT="NEW" ALIGN="TOP">
<A HREF="http://ewi.ewi.org/">
Edison Welding Institute</A></H3>

<P>The Edison Welding Institute is an industrially driven,
technology focused research, development and technology transfer Center
whose mission is to advance and apply materials joining technology for
the economic benefit of industry.</P>

<HR>
<P><A HREF="/index.htm">
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/b_arrow.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
Back to IAMS Home Page</A></P>
