<HEAD>
<TITLE>SBDC Page</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Glenn Benz, 15-Jan-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/logo.gif" ALT="IAMS" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE">
<H1>Small Business Development Center</H1></CENTER>

<HR>
<H4>Comprehensive management assistance for your small business is
offered on a one-on-one basis through the University of Cincinnati's
Small Business Development Center (SBDC). The center provides assistance
to established small businesses as well as to persons starting a new
business. Areas of assistance include business plan development,
financial analysis and forecasting; marketing and sales planning;
selling to the government and more. The SBDC welcomes all small business
entrepreneurs and is comitted to providing high quality, confidential
and effective consultation, and referrals all at no charge.</H4>

<HR>
<CENTER>
<H2>SBDC Provides</H2></CENTER><OL>
<LI>Assistance in the start-up and development of new and existing
businesses</LI>
<LI>Expertise and guidance regarding selling to the government</LI>
<LI>Low cost seminars and courses</LI></OL>

<HR>
<CENTER>
<H2>Financial Resources and Loan Packaging</H2></CENTER>
<H4>The SBDC <I>does not</I>make loans, however, the Center <I>does</I> have
information about various financial resources that make loans available to new
and existing small businesses. The SBDC will help identify the appropriate
financial resources and assist in loan packaging.</H4>

<HR>
<CENTER><H2>Government Marketing Assistance</H2></CENTER>
<H4>The SBDC-GMA program helps small businesses sell to the government. This
includes identifying government agencies that purchase your goods or services,
a computerized bid-matching service, a Military Specifications Library, a
complete Federal Acquisition Regulations Library and access to historical
purchasing information.</H4>

<HR>
<CENTER><H2>Workshops and Seminars</H2></CENTER>
<H4>The SBDC works closely with other resources to provide workshops and
seminars for the small business community. The topics of theses programs
are designed to address many aspects of operating and maintaining a
small business <I>profitably</I>.</H4>

<HR>
<CENTER><H2>Small Business Clearinghouse</H2></CENTER>
<H4>The SBDC developed and manages a data base of resources specially designed
to assist small businesses. Whatever your business challenge, we can identify
the appropriate organization to answere your questions and assist your business
</H4>

<HR>
<P>For more information on these services contact
<A HREF="/people/owens.htm">Mike Owens</A>.</P>

<HR>
<P><A HREF="/index.htm">
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/b_arrow.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
Back to IAMS Home Page</A></P>
