<HEAD>
<TITLE>MVMEC Home Page</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Glenn Benz, 15-Jan-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/logo.gif" ALT="IAMS" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE">
<H1>Miami Valley Manufacturing Extension Center</H1></CENTER>

<HR>
<CENTER><STRONG><H1>MVMEC WORKS FOR YOU</H1></STRONG></CENTER>

<P><STRONG>MVMEC</STRONG> is an organization helping Southwest Ohio
manufacturers achieve bottom line benefits.  MVMEC strives as a single
point-of-contact for experts in: manufacturing operations and
technology; business and general managment; quality; training and
education; defense conversion; pollution prevention; waste reduction;
and obtaining financial assistance.  Our engineers have a wealth of
experience in industry and business.  For specific problem solving,
MVMEC can tap the expertise of its partner organizations which come
from industry, government and institutions of higher learning.</P>

<P><H3>Company-Specific Services:  Focused, Affordable, Effective</H3>
Why MVMEC -- Success in manufacturing involves more than hard work.
If it only took hard work, all manufacturers would be wealthy -- but
we know better.  Success in manufactuirng involves doing things right
and being sure that you are doing the right things.  That's easy to
say, but exceedingly more difficult to do.  This is where MVMEC can
help.</P>

<P><B>Working Together</B> - MVMEC field engineers work with owners,
managers and work force representatives in a professional and
collegial mannger.  Confidentiality is assured.</P>

<P><B>Assessment</B> -- An accurate and methodical process to learn
how a company measures up to its competitors.</P>

<P><B>Individiualized Assistance</B> -- MVMEC assisted projects can
range from several hours of no charge consulting services to
affordable, comprehensive improvement programs.</P>

<P><B>Group Activities </B>-- Take advantage of the information
exchange which takes place when associating with others in your
industry.</P>

<P><B>MVMEC Goal</B> -- To increase the competitive advantage of
manufacturing industries in southwest Ohio.</P>

<P><B>MVMEC Method</B> -- Assess a company's current operations and
systems.  Identify barrriers to progress as well as opportunities for
growth.  Develop solutions tailored to company goals.</P>

<P><B>MVMEC Product</B> -- The tenet of the MVMEC is to serve as
southwest Ohio's one stop shop for all services and assistance
pertaining to manufacturing and busines operations for small and
medium sized enterprises including defense-dependent firms desiring to
transition to commercial markets.  The final product will be an
improved operation that will result in a favorable and measurable
economic impact on each company's bottom line.</P>

<P><B>Meeting the Challenge</B> -- MVMEC can help companies make
informed decisions about the changes required to get from where they
are to where they need to be.</P>

<P>For more information on these services contact
<A HREF="/people/sauter.htm"> Mark Sauter</A>, Director, IAMS-MVMEC or 
<A HREF="/people/dchalk@mvmec.org">Dave Chalk</A>, Director, MVMEC</P>

<P>
<LI>Mark Sauter</LI>
<LI>IAMS-MVMEC</LI>
<LI>1111 Edison Drive</LI>
<LI>Cincinnati, OH  45216</LI>
<LI>513.948.2000</LI>
<LI>800.345.4482</LI></P>

<P><LI>Dave Chalk</LI>
<LI>Miami Valley MEC</LI>
<LI>3155 Research Boulevard</LI>
<LI>Kettering, OH  45240</LI>
<LI>937.258.6190</LI>
<LI>800.55.MVMEC</LI></P>

<HR>
