<HEAD>
<!-- Changed by: Glenn Benz, 12-Jan-1996 -->
<TITLE>Available Jobs at IAMS</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.00">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Jean Fredette">
</HEAD>

<CENTER><H1><B>JOBS AVAILABLE AT IAMS</B></H1></CENTER>
<CENTER><H2>Check here for all open postions</H2></CENTER>
<HR>

<P><H3>POSITION:  MVMEC FIELD REPRESENTATIVE-PROJECT</H3></P>

<P><B><I>PRIMARY FUNCTION</I></B>:	

Manage third party providers of services to IAMS clients, perform limited amounts of less-than-eight-hour, no fee technical assistance in support of the activities of MVMEC Field Representatives-Sales and team with a Manufacturing SBDC Business Analyst in completing high impact assessments of area manufacturing companies.  In addition,  contact area manufacturers with fewer than ten employees in an effort to establish productive working relationships with the owners and/or key managers of these companies.

Position requires at least three years in a manufacturing environment, with an emphasis on engineering, machining and/or quality control systems.  Candidate must have excellent interpersonal, writing and verbal skills, and excellent team building skills; must be proficient in Word, Excel and Powerpoint.  Engineering degree preferred.</P>

<HR>

<P><H3>POSITION TITLE:	MVMEC FIELD REPRESENTATIVE-SALES</H3></P>

<P><B><I>PRIMARY FUNCTION</I></B>:	

Employ consultative selling techniques to establish close working relationships with a target group of manufacturers within Hamilton, Butler, Warren and Clermont Counties.  The Field Representative-Sales will develop advisory relationships with top executives of these manufacturers to facilitate needs assessment and the identification of appropriate services and/or products which can be delivered by IAMS or third parties resources. 

Position requires at least five years successful experience selling to manufacturing enterprises, preferably in the technical services area, excellent interpersonal and communication skills and the ability to excel in achieving team-based metrics.  A college degree is preferred.</P>

<HR>

<P><H3>POSITION:  MANUFACTURING SBDC BUSINESS ANALYST</P></H3>

<P><B><I>PRIMARY FUNCTION:</I></B>

Manage third party providers of services to IAMS clients, perform limited amounts of less-than-eight-hour, no-fee technical assistance and team with an IAMS MVMEC Field Representative in completing High Impact Assessments of area manufacturing companies.  In addition, will also contact area manufacturers with fewer than ten employees in an effort to establish productive working relationships with the owners and/or key managers of these companies.  

Position requires at least three or more years in a manufacturing environment, preferably in industrial marketing; ability to compute and interpret financial ratios and to apply other traditional financial analysis tools. Candidate must have excellent interpersonal, writing and verbal skills, and excellent team building skills. Must be proficient in Word, Excel and Powerpoint.  Relevant undergraduate degree required,  MBA  a plus.</P>

<HR>

<P><H3>POSITION:  MVMEC TRAINING/WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT SPECIALIST</P></H3>

<P><B><I>PRIMARY FUNCTION:</I></B>

Develop mechanisms for accurately assessing manufacturing entitiesí needs for specific training programs.  Identify available third party training resources to address these needs.  Negotiate mutually beneficial arrangements with identified third parties for the delivery of training services to manufacturers.  Formulate marketing strategies for and assist in the sale of training programs to potential purchasers of these services.  

Position requires at least three years in a manufacturing environment, preferably in an area closely related to or directly involved in personnel training programs;  experience in project management, including full P/L accountability.  Candidate must have excellent interpersonal, writing and verbal skills; proficiency in Word, Excel and Powerpoint; college degree required, graduate degree a plus.</P>

<HR>

<P><H3>WE ARE CURRENTLY RECRUITING FOR THE POSITION OF ACCOUNTING ASSISTANT.  IF INTERESTED, PLEASE CONTACT MANAGER OF HUMAN RESOURCES BY NOVEMBER 8.</H3></P>

<P><H3>POSITION TITLE:	ACCOUNTING ASSISTANT</P></H3>

<P><B><I>PRIMARY FUNCTION:</I></B>

Perform accounting related functions.  Operate under the general guidance of the Accounting Manager within confines of existing financial and Institute policies, practices and procedures.

This position requires two to three years experience as an accounting clerk or bookkeeper with concentration in A/P.  Must have excellent data entry skills.  Must be familiar with computerized accounting systems, Solomon preferred.  Experience with Microsoft Excel and Word a plus. Two year accounting degree preferred, but not required.</P>

<HR>

<P><H3>POSITION TITLE:  INSIDE SALES - SOFTWARE</P></H3>

<P><B><I>PRIMARY FUNCTION:</I></B>

We are seeking an Inside Sales Rep to sell software products.  Successful candidate will have a proven track record in responding to and qualifying leads.  Responsibilities include fulfilling orders, tracking software maintenance agreements, maintaining a customer database and handling invoicing and inventory for this fast-paced software division. This position also coordinates trade shows and provides software marketing support.

Requirements:  Two years successful track record in telephone sales, lead generation and follow-up; demonstrated knowledge of PC-based software; the ability to explain features and benefits; and knowledge of Microsoft Word and database experience.

If you like a fast-paced, professional environment and have strong inside sales and marketing support skills, please send a cover letter, resume and salary requirements.</P>

<P><B><CENTER>EEO M/F/D/V</P>

<P>Please mail or email resume to:
Manager, Human Resources
1111 Edison Drive
Cincinnati, OH  45216</P>
<P>email to:  webmaster@iams.org</CENTER></B></P>


