<DOCHDR>
http://viking.iams.org:80/caet/faq.htm 206.112.215.24 19970110024945 text/html 5435
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
Date: Fri, 10 Jan 1997 02:52:19 GMT
Server: NCSA/1.4.2
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE></TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Greg Hume">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#0000FF">

<CENTER><P><B><FONT COLOR="#400040"><FONT SIZE=+1>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</FONT></FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="logo.gif" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=100></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B>IAMS</B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B>CENTER FOR APPLIED ENVIRONMENTAL TECHNOLOGIES</B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Waste and Energy Reduction Assessments and
Project Management</FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="blue2.gif" HEIGHT=8 WIDTH=581></P></CENTER>

<P><B>What is the Center for Applied Environmental Technologies (CAET)?</B></P>

<UL>
<LI>CAET is part of the Institute of Advanced Manufacturing Sciences, Inc.
(IAMS), a not-for-profit organization funded in part by the Ohio Department
of Development and in part by private industry </LI>

<LI>Our mission is to make regional manufacturers more competitive </LI>

<LI>CAET contributes to this mission by offering industry technical assistance
in waste and energy reduction</LI>
</UL>

<P><B>Why Should I Be Interested in IAMSí Waste and/or Energy Reduction
Assessments?</B> <BR>
(Waste and energy assessments are done separately)</P>

<UL>
<LI>To reduce your companyís wastes and energy usage </LI>

<LI>To save your company money </LI>

<LI>To help with your environmental compliance </LI>

<LI>To prevent raw materials from becoming wastes </LI>

<LI>To free up labor hours</LI>
</UL>

<P><B>How Can IAMSí Staff Help My Company?</B></P>

<UL>
<LI>Our staff of five full-time and five part-time engineers and scientists
with expertise in manufacturing processes, chemical processing, recycling,
environmental regulations and treatment technologies is available as a
resource for your company </LI>

<LI>Our staff has helped 95 companies develop waste and energy reduction
options over the past four years </LI>

<LI>CAETís assessments have averaged annual projected savings of $90,000
per company</LI>
</UL>

<P><B>How Do the Waste and Energy Reduction Assessments Fit into the Waste
and Energy Reduction Process?</B></P>

<UL>
<LI>They are the first step in development of a waste and energy reduction
program for your plant T</LI>

<LI>The assessment will provide a prioritized list of opportunities for
reducing wastes and energy usage </LI>

<LI>After the assessment, your company assumes responsibility for continuing
the waste or energy reduction program </LI>

<LI>Your company may chose to implement specific waste or energy reduction
options after investigating the technical feasibility </LI>

<LI>After the assessment, our staff can be called on for project management
support </LI>
</UL>

<P><B>What Happens During a Waste or Energy Reduction Assessment?</B></P>

<UL>
<LI>Our staff visits your facility to look at your information on types
and quantities of your wastes or energy costs and tour your manufacturing
process </LI>

<LI>We develop suggestions for waste or energy reductions with estimates
of potential savings and resources for implementation </LI>

<LI>CAET makes a second visit to present the results of brainstorming waste
or energy reduction options to decide which options to pursue in more detail
</LI>

<LI>CAET will also provide your company with additional information on
selected options, and supply names of vendors or engineers who can assist
in design and implementation </LI>

<LI>CAET can provide project management services</LI>
</UL>

<P><B>How Much Time Will the Assessment Require?</B></P>

<UL>
<LI>Prior to our visit, we ask your company to fill out a pre-assessment
questionnaire that helps us make better use of our time during our visit.
We expect that this will take about one half hour of your time </LI>

<LI>Our initial visit normally take from two to four hours, depending on
the size of the company </LI>

<LI>Our second visit normally takes between one and two hours </LI>

<LI>Implementing suggestions from the waste or energy reduction assessment
may require a significant investment of your companyís time and money,
which should be offset by future cost savings</LI>
</UL>

<P><B>Who Pays for Assessments?</B></P>

<UL>
<LI>IAMS is a not-for-profit organization</LI>

<LI>Fees are charged to cover costs, but grant funding may be available
to smaller companies or within certain geographic areas to subsidize fees
</LI>

<LI>There is no charge for a consultation visit</LI>
</UL>

<P><B>How Many Assessments Has CAET Done and What Have the Results Been?</B></P>

<UL>
<LI>Over the past four years, we have worked with over 95 Ohio companies
to offer suggestions for waste and energy reduction with an average annual
projected savings of $90K each </LI>

<LI>All of these companies have implemented some of our suggestions for
waste or energy reduction</LI>
</UL>

<P><B>What Do We Need to Do to Schedule an Assessment?</B></P>

<UL>
<LI>Call Trent Wall at (513) 948-2071 to discuss and schedule an assessment</LI>
</UL>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
