<BODY TEXT="#FFFFFF" BGCOLOR="#000080" LINK="#FFFF00" VLINK="#8080FF" ALINK="#FF00FF">

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>RICK GELLERT</FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<P>Rick Gellert has fifteen years of manufacturing and project management
experience in Facilities/Plant Engineering with IBM, Carrier Air Conditioning
Corp., Norton Co. and Bowen McGlaughlin York. He has prepared utility budgets
and project estimates, developed capital plans, and supervised engineers,
consultants and contractors. He has direct experience with HVAC, dust collection,
process and utilty piping systems. Rick has installed a waste treatment
facility and coordinated major roofing and facilities projects.</P>

<P>Mr. Gellert earned an Associate of Applied Science in Mechanical Technology
at Onondaga Communiy College and a Bachelor of Science in Mechanical Engineering
at Syracuse University. He has taken graduate MBA courses at Union College,
Schenectady, NY.</P>

