<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Green Cutting Fluid</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Glenn Benz, 15-Jan-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/logo.gif" ALT="IAMS" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE">
<H1>Machining Xcellence to Develop Green Cutting Fluid</H1><IMG SRC="/graphics/blue2.gif"></CENTER>

<P>An EPA funded project whose goal is to develop an environmentally friendly coolant, "green" coolant, has begun with initial contacts to companies of all sizes who use and manufacture metal working fluids.  The ultimate goal is to promote and/or modify a coolant which has the best working properites of existing process fluids but lasts longer and requires less disposal by frequency and amount.</P>

<P>Listed below are the companies of the environmentally friendly people who have accepted the challenge to become a part of the Industry Advisory Group  (IAG) who will help guide these efforts to a successful conclusion:</P>

<UL>

<LI>Michigan Technological University </LI>
<LI>Defiance Precision Products </LI>
<LI>SPEEDFAM</LI>
<LI>Cincinnati Milacron</LI>
<LI>Monsanto</LI>
<LI>Texaco</LI>
<LI>Imperial Oil/Exxon Research Department</LI>
<LI>Positrol, Inc.</LI>
<LI>Cast-Fab Technologies, Inc.</LI>
<LI>Wagstaff</LI>
<LI>Dana Corporation-ATRG</LI>
<LI>University of Texas</LI>
<LI>R.E. Dye Manufacturing Corporation</LI>
<LI>Inland Steel Bar Co.</LI>
<LI>The Timken Company</LI>
<LI>Richards Industries Inc.</LI>
<LI>Parker Hannifin Corporation</LI>
<LI>Osteo Biologies</LI>
<LI>HiLite Industries, Inc.</LI>
<LI>Boeing Commercial Airplan Group/Operations Technology</LI>
<LI>Navistar International</LI>
<LI>The Metalworking Group</LI>
<LI>Relton Corporation</LI>
<LI>Meyer Tool Inc.</LI>
<LI>Maine Metal Products Association</LI>
<LI>A.W. Chesterton</LI>
<LI>Aeroquip Corporation</LI>
<LI>Black Clawson-Shartle Division</LI>
<LI>Ashot Ashkelon Industries, Inc.</LI>
<LI>The Lubrizol Corporation</LI>
<LI>General Motors</LI>
</UL>
 
<P> We will continue looking for additional companies who share an interest in this project up until the kickoff on April 17 (Manufacturer's Meeting) and April 18 (User's Meeting) at IAMS.  If you are interested or would like more information, please call <A HREF="/people/finn.htm">Mike Finn </A> or Tom McClure, Machining Technology Engineers, at 1-800-345-4482</A>.</P>

