<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Energy Home Page</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<CENTER><P><!-- Changed by: Glenn Benz, 15-Jan-1996 --><IMG SRC="/graphics/logo.gif" ALT="IAMS"  ALIGN=ABSCENTER>
</P></CENTER>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>ENERGY EFFICIENCY ASSESSMENTS</H1>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="/graphics/blue2.gif" > </P></CENTER>

<UL>
<CENTER><P><B>BENEFITS &amp; IMPACT</B> </P></CENTER>

<P>Assessments focus on reducing PEAK LOAD and ENERGY COSTS through the
identification of energy conservation opportunities such as load shifting,
energy efficient technologies, and other appropriate techniques</P>

<CENTER><P><B>OVERVIEW OF THE PROCESS</B> </P></CENTER>

<P>Manufacturing or ELECTRICAL Engineers typically spend TWO to THREE days
on site investigating: </P>

<UL>
<LI>Process &amp; equipment energy use through extensive on-site metering</LI>

<LI>Lighting &amp; HVAC System efficiencies</LI>

<LI>Thermal temperature zones &amp; insulation</LI>
</UL>

<CENTER><P><B>DELIVERABLE</B> </P></CENTER>

<P>Company's receive a final report &amp; presentation highlighting the
company's current ENERGY PROFILE and Prioritized opportunity areas for
Improvement. Regional vendors and appropriate resources for implementation
assistance are identified along with initial project plans and project
paybacks</P>

<P>
<HR></P>

<P>For more information on these services contact our Energy Specialist
<A HREF="../people/gellert.htm">Rick Gellert.</A></P>

<P><HR>
<P><A HREF="/index.htm">
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/b_arrow.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
Back to IAMS Home Page</A></P>
<FONT SIZE=2><B><I>
<P>
<A HREF="mailto:webmaster@iams.org">
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/mailbox.gif" ALIGN="LEFT"></A>
Please mail any comments, suggestions or requests to:<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:webmaster@iams.org">webmaster@iams.org</A>
</P>
<P>
This page was last modified on 04-Nov-96
</P>
</I></B></FONT>
</P>
