<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Waste Home Page</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Glenn Benz, 15-Jan-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/logo.gif" ALT="IAMS" ALIGN="ABSMIDDLE">
<H1>WASTE MINIMIZATION ASSESSMENTS</H1>
</CENTER>


<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/blue2.gif"></CENTER>

<UL>


<CENTER><STRONG>BENEFITS & IMPACT</STRONG></CENTER>
<P>Assessments focus on reducing WASTE DISPOSAL & RAW MATERIAL COSTS, and
LIABILITIES through the identification of material substitutions, process
improvements, recycling, advanced technologies and other appropriate techniques
</P>

<CENTER><STRONG>OVERVIEW OF THE PROCESS</STRONG></CENTER>
<P>MANUFACTURING, ENVIRONMENTAL or CHEMICAL Engineers typically spend ONE to
TWO days on site investigating:
<UL>
<LI>Raw Materials used production</LI>
<LI>Process Waste Streams & Costs</LI>
<LI>Specific production processes, technologies, and practices</LI>
</UL>
</P>  

<CENTER><STRONG>DELIVERABLE</STRONG></CENTER>
<P>Companies receive a final report & presentation highlighting the company's
current WASTE STREAMS, their associated costs, and prioritized opportunity
areas for Improvement. Specific projects, regional vendors and appropriate
resources for implementation assistance are identified along with initial
project plans and project paybacks.</P>

<HR>
<P>For more information on these services contact
<A HREF="/people/clement1.htm">Sally Clement</A>.</P>

<HR>
<P><A HREF="/index.htm">
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/b_arrow.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
Back to IAMS Home Page</A></P>
<FONT SIZE=2><B><I>
<P>
<A HREF="mailto:webmaster@iams.org">
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/mailbox.gif" ALIGN="LEFT"></A>
Please mail any comments, suggestions or requests to:<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:webmaster@iams.org">webmaster@iams.org</A>
</P>
