<HEAD>
<TITLE>M. Eugene Merchant, Ph. D.</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Glenn Benz, 10-Jan-1996 -->
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H2>M. Eugene Merchant, Ph. D.</H2>
<H3>Senior Consultant</H3>

A recent inductee into the Automation Hall of Fame, <B>Dr. M. Eugene Merchant</B>
is an internationally recognized authority on the global scene in the science, technology and human resource aspects of manufacturing, manufacturing systems and the future of manufacturing.
</P>

<p><center><IMG SRC="/people/merchant.gif"></center><center><b> Dr M. Eugene Merchant</b></center></p>
<p> 
Often called the "Father of Research, Development and Implementation" of the concepts of the systems approach to manufacturing, <B>Dr. Merchant </B> divides his time between attending leading manufacturing research conferences around the world, visiting manufacturing facilities and writing the <I> Window Reports</I>.
</p>
<p>

<B>Dr. Merchant</B> is Senior Consultant at the Institute of Advanced Manufacuring Sciences.  He utilizes his 50+ years of experience to summarize and evaluate the findings of cooperative research activities, international confrences and seminars, with particular emphasis on those organized or endorsed by the International Institution for Production Engineering Research (CIRP).
</p>
<HR>
<P>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:merchant@iams.org">merchant@iams.org</A><BR>
TEL: (513) 948-2067
</P>
<HR>

</BODY>
</HTML>
