<head>
<title>P2IRIS Document Library</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

</head>
<body>

<p><img src="giffiles/libhead.gif" border=0></p>

<h3><img src="giffiles/golden.gif" border=0>Chemical and general reference</h3>
<p>
<P>
<ul><A HREF="http://law.house.gov/cfr.htm" >Federal Register Search</A>
<P>
<A HREF="188.htm">Listing of 188 Hazardous Air Pollutants</A>

<P>
<A HREF="msds.htm">Material Safety Data Sheets</A>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.cchem.berkeley.edu/Table/index.html">Periodic Table On-line from UC Berkeley</A>
<BR></ul>



<h3><img src="giffiles/golden.gif" border=0>Metal Finishing Related Publications</h3>
<p>
<br>
<ul><strong>&quot;A Pollution Prevention Resource Manual for Metal Finishers&quot;</strong>
<a HREF="metalfin.htm">(View)</a>  </ul></p>
<p><ul><img src="giffiles/p2man.gif" hspace=20 border=0  height=104 width =80 align=left ></ul>

<p>This publication describes cost effective pollution prevention techniques that 
have been implemented by metal finishers in the Greater Cincinnati Metropolitan Area.  
The techniques including cost effective changes in materials, processes, or 
management practices have been demonstrated and proven to provide environmental and 
economic benefits.
<br></p>



<br>
<br><p><ul><strong>&quot;A Company Performance Self-Assessment Tool for Metal Finishers&quot;</strong>
<a HREF="http://www.iti.org/ee/eem/selfasse/emc3.htm">(view)</a></p>
<P>This study describes the Performance Self-Assessment Tool for metal finishers designed by the Energy, Environment and Manufacturing Project (EEM). A primary objective of the EEM assessment is to identify and evaluate opportunities for
energy efficiency, pollution prevention/waste reduction, and improved manufacturing methods resulting in increased competitiveness for small- and medium-sized manufacturing firms. </ul>



<br>
<br><p><ul><strong>&quot;Enviro$en$e Metal Finishing Content Guide&quot;</strong>
<a HREF="http://www.seattle.battelle.org/es-guide/metals/metals.htm">(Download from Enviro$en$e server)</a></ul></p>

<p>
<ul>Metal finishers have many opportunities for cost-effective pollution prevention, ranging 
from using non-solvent and detergent-based methods for preparing surfaces, to efficient 
plating bath management and work management techniques that can help you save on material 
and labor costs. Enviro$en$e can provide you with timely information on many of these 
topics. This Content Guide provides you with several ways to navigate the wealth of 
information related to the metal finishing industry.
<br></p>


<br>
<br><p><strong>&quot;Enviro$en$e Fabricated Metal Products Industry Sector Notebook&quot;</strong>
<a HREF="http://es.inel.gov/comply/sector/index.htm">(Download from Enviro$en$e server)</a></p>

<p>
Multimedia summary, industrial process, pollution outputs, TRI data, pollution prevention, 
federal regulations, compliance history, compliance assistance, voluntary programs, 
electroplating, anodizing, conversion coatings, organic coatings, metal forming, chromium, 
cadmium, nickel, zinc, cyanide, VOCs.
<br></p>



<p>
<br>
<div align=center><p><img src="giffiles/libbar.gif" border=0  height=45 width =334 >
