<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Sally Clement</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#003366 text=#FFFFFF link=#ffff00 vlink=#909000> 
<BODY>

<center><h3>SARA J. CLEMENT</h3></center>


Sally Clement is the Director  of  Manufacturing Efficiency and  acts as  Manager of the Center for Applied Environmental Technologies at the Institute of Advanced Manufacturing Sciences, Inc.  Since joining IAMS some four years ago, she has participated in developing a pollution prevention technical assistance program serving the southern Ohio area.  </p>

<p>Ms. Clement has earned two Master of Science degrees:  one from the University of Cincinnati in environmental science, and another from Syracuse University in geology.  Before joining IAMS, Ms. Clement spent three years in the environmental consulting industry, working primarily on soil and groundwater remediation projects.  Prior to that, she worked in an environmental compliance position for industry, primarily working on water and hazardous waste issues.  She has also worked in academic environmental research and as a geologist, and has taught geology, earth science, and physical science.</p>

<p>Ms. Clement is focusing her efforts at IAMS on pollution prevention technical assess-ments, working on coordinating and scheduling the activities of several retired engineers and full-time employees working on waste and energy assessments.  The purpose of the assessments is to develop cost-effective methods of waste reduction for industry.









<P>E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:clement@iams.org">clement@iams.org</A></P>


</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
