<HR>
<h1>Welcome to JDUPO!</h1>
<HR>

<h2>What's New</h2>

<h4><IMG SRC="image/rdsq.gif"> A new solicitation has been announced to reduce the operations and support cost
of the Department of Defense by inserting commercial technology into fielded
systems.  The Commercial Operations and Support Savings Initiative Program Description and Solicitation is <A HREF="cossi/intro.html">here</a></h4>

<h4><IMG SRC="image/rdsq.gif"> Additional information concerning the solicitation is also available from other websites:<P>

<UL>
<LI>An electronic version of the Commerce Business Daily <A HREF="http://www.darpa.mil/baa/PA97-12">announcement</a> is available from <A HREF="http://www.darpa.mil">DARPA</a>
<LI>A Department of Defense <A HREF="http://www.dtic.mil/defenselink/news/Jan97/b011497_bt015-97.html">news release</a> and <A HREF="http://www.dtic.mil/defenselink/news/Jan97/t011597_t0114at.html">briefing</a> are available from <A HREF="http://www.dtic.mil/defenselink/">DefenseLINK</a>

 
</UL></h4>


<H2>Recent Information</H2>

<IMG SRC="image/rdsq.gif"> The <A HREF="info/duap_fact.html">Dual Use Applications Program</a> builds on lessons learned from the Technology Reinvestment Project.<P>
<IMG SRC="image/rdsq.gif"> With the establishment of the<A HREF=info/jdupo_fact.html> Joint Dual Use Program Office</A>, no further <A HREF=info/trp_fact.html>Technology Reinvestment Project</a> competitions are planned.<p>

<IMG SRC="image/rdsq.gif"> The <A HREF="select95/95desc.html">winners</a> of the TRP FY95 solicitation were announced on December 23, 1995.</a><p>

<IMG SRC="image/rdsq.gif"> See the TRP <A HREF="annual_95/cover.html"> report</A> on the projects selected for funding under 
 the Technology Reinvestment Project (TRP) in 1993 and 1994<p>

