<HEAD>

<TITLE>Joint Dual-Use Program Office</TITLE>


</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<h2>Fact Sheet: The Joint Dual Use Program Office</h2>
<HR> 
In December 1995, the Office of the Secretary of Defense, DARPA, and the Army, Navy and Air Force signed a Memorandum of Understanding establishing the Joint Dual-Use Program Office (JDUPO).  The new office reports to the Director of Defense Research and Engineering and will develop a military-based, DoD-wide approach to dual-use technology development for more effective and affordable military weapon systems.  It will select technology focus areas, offer solicitations, and conduct competitions.  In addition, the office will monitor ongoing TRP efforts from earlier competitions.<p>

The Office will be staffed initially with an Office Director (to be provided by DARPA) and three Service Deputies (one from the Army, Navy and Air Force).  Funding for the first year (FY97) will be provided by DARPA, with future funding to be provided by the Director for Defense Research and Engineering.  Additional staffing and future funding levels have yet to be determined.  The civilian agencies previously part of TRP are not parties to the official Memorandum of Understanding, but DoD hopes to continue its excellent cooperation with the civilian technical experts.<p> 

<!--The JDUPO will continue the tradition of selecting projects competitively.  During 1996, the JDUPO will finalize plans for the FY97 competition, and choose eight to 10 technology focus areas for the competition.<P>-->
<HR>
